title: Moonflower
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2GwtqU1

by K_K_TiBal

Castiel is not a very good witch.
He’s just not.
He struggles with potions, illusions, divination - everything that makes a witch respectable, and his familiar - Dean - definitely deserves better than him.
When Dean falls under a curse that seems to affect his shape-shifting abilities, Castiel and Dean begin to run out of money, and Castiel decides the best thing they can do is go after a rare Moonflower to help get themselves back on their feet.
The journey could be dangerous, especially considering Castiel’s less-than-ideal abilities and Dean’s curse, but with a little luck, it will all be worth it in the end.

title: 11 inch Heroine
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2GvSt9V

by Bluewingeddean

THE PLOT AND DIOLOGUE OF THE MOVIE 10 INCH HERO.
-
Dean moves to a seaside town to get away from his old life and Sams basement. He’s an artist and needs inspiration which is just what the beach can do… that and he gave his son away when he was a teenager, seeing an art award in the paper for a ‘Ben Novak’ that looks exactly like him and has the same name as his son.
He meets the father, Cas. And things hit off. Is it his son? Will they be a family? Will everything turn out how they want it?
Fluff and smutt included ;)

There are also other random relationships going on with some fun asf backstories.

-
You definitely don’t have to have seen TIH to read this, it’s probably funner and more surprise if you haven’t.
If you have it’s like wow yeah that happened in the movie
Lol

summary: Six Sentence Sunday is a writing thing where, on Sunday, you post six sentences from an unfinished work. It can be a new fic, a...
body:
Six Sentence Sunday is a writing thing where, on Sunday, you post six sentences from an unfinished work. It can be a new fic, a new chapter of a WIP, or even something you’re not sure you’ll ever post. Choose an excerpt from any section (and it doesn’t have to be six sentences) and post it, letting people know what it belongs to or indicating that it’s something you’re working on.

Scene from an Alt!Dimension

Chapter 5: Click Your Heels, Dorothy

Summary: In that alternate universe, the final battle between angels and humankind was fought and won. Now there are only a few loose ends to tie up – like how to get back home and save the world. Alternative Season 13 finale the fandom and characters deserved. Final chapter, WIP 2/17/2019

***

The battle had come to its desired if unanticipated conclusion. They had won.

In the expanse of wasteland and condemning spires, some crowned with tatters of cloth and bone, Crowley stood breathing shallowing as the last thrum of slaughter faded into eerie calm.

The blind terror and bombardment of the all-encompassing night had given way to an ashen, bleak morning, diluted and grainy, as every morning had been in this discolored reality. A reluctant draft swirled dust around in the haze, the disconcerting stillness tempered by the moans of wounded and dying.

Strewn across the wasteland were mangled forms and crumbled corpses, dark and contorted shapes stagnant in their absence of life. Angels’ vessels too, those hollowed out husks of the prostituted devout, victims of predatory divinity. Interwoven charcoal outlines of carbonized wings patterned the valley, like black, gossamer imprints stamped into the dirt. They laid across the wrenched entrails and shorn limbs like dusky funeral shrouds.

At Crowley’s feet lay his own corpse.

‘… He had heard about talking to plants in the early seventies, on Radio Four, and thought it was an excellent idea. Although talking is perhaps the wrong word for what Crowley did.

What he did was put the fear of God into them.

More precisely, the fear of Crowley.’

title: good-omens-new | Media
description:
A while back I made a super popular post about the Good Omens musical that is being developed in Australia and that I was lucky enough to see a developmental reading of. Even for something that is still in the process of being developed, it was already exceptional. The songs were catchy, the lines perfect and the performances so in line with the essence of what makes Good Omens GREAT. 

I had a LOT of people express interest in finding out more about it.

I just discovered the link above which actually has some videos from the one I got to see. For anyone interested, check out the link and enjoy!

summary:
Person 1: Things are the loudest when you want them to be the quietest
Person 2: Like microwaves
Person 1: And sneaking around...
body:
Person 1: Things are the loudest when you want them to be the quietest

Person 2: Like microwaves

Person 1: And sneaking around after hours

Person 2: Getting out of bed without waking up your partner

Person 3: *Whispers under breath* My mind

Person 2: What was that, Person 3?

Person 3: Nothing

Person 1: Person 3, you are an example of something that is too quiet when needing to be loud

Person 3: *screams* Is this loud enough for ya!

Person 1 and 2’s ears bleeding while they run out of the room

Person 3 left in the room maniacally laughing as they slowly sink down through the floor to go see Crowley in hell

summary: supernatural season eight 》episode twenty two 》clip show what's the line? "saving people, hunting things – the family business."...
caption:
supernatural season eight 》episode twenty two 》clip show

what’s the line? “saving people, hunting things – the family business.” well, I think the people you save, they’re how you justify your pathetic little lives. the alcoholism, the collateral damage, the pain you’ve caused – the one thing that allows you to sleep at night, the one thing is knowing that these folks are out there, still out there happy and healthy because of you, you great, big, bloody heroes! sarah? they’re your life’s work, and I’m going to rip it apart piece by piece because I can, because you can’t stop me, and because when they’re all gone, what will you have left?
